{"repo": "agiresearch/AIOS", "pull_number": 509, "instance_id": "agiresearch__AIOS-509", "issue_numbers": [508], "base_commit": "ea12926b0a0faa47a80763e4e26ac58a7c0354e1", "patch": "diff --git a/.dockerignore b/.dockerignore\nindex e19db719..19502fcd 100644\n--- a/.dockerignore\n+++ b/.dockerignore\n@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@\n-__pycache__\n+**/__pycache__\n venv\n env\n .github\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Misc] Possible .dockerignore misconfiguration\n### Anything you want to discuss about aios.\n\nHello, and thank you for your work on this repository!\n\nAs part of my research, I am analyzing how developers configure .dockerignore in popular repositories.\n\nDuring my analysis, I noticed that `/.dockerignore` might have been written under the assumption that .dockerignore and .gitignore follow the same pattern semantics, while they actually differ.[^1] In particular, the following pattern drew my attention:\n\nhttps://github.com/agiresearch/AIOS/blob/9071a18c79e73d945e7050ddad8549794180f80d/.dockerignore#L1\n\nAccording to Docker's specification, this pattern matches `__pycache__` only in the top-level directory. (To ignore `__pycache__` in any directory, the .dockerignore file needs to list `**/__pycache__`)\n\n**Was this pattern written intentionally?** If not, I'd be happy to submit a pull request to adjust it :)\n\nAnd if possible, could you tell me whether you were aware of the difference between .dockerignore and .gitignore? (I would like to know whether the differences are generally well recognized, or if they tend to slip developers' minds.)\n\nThank you again for maintaining this repository!\n\n", "hints_text": "Hi @tomokinakamaru,\n\nGood catch, you\u2019re right that .dockerignore and .gitignore differ, and the current __pycache__ pattern only matches at the top level. That wasn\u2019t intentional; we do want to ignore __pycache__ recursively.\n\nA PR to fix this (e.g., using **/__pycache__) would be much appreciated. Thanks for spotting it and for raising awareness of this subtle difference!\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi @tomokinakamaru,\n\nGood catch, you\u2019re right that .dockerignore and .gitignore differ, and the current __pycache__ pattern only matches at the top level. That wasn\u2019t intentional; we do want to ignore __pycache__ recursively.\n\nA PR to fix this (e.g., using **/__pycache__) would be much appreciated. Thanks for spotting it and for raising awareness of this subtle difference!\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/agiresearch/AIOS/commit/b88c335bb159b02ce4abb6f51cd213d7be257f54"], "created_at": "2025-10-14T00:59:51Z"}
